        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Olaf Faaland",
          "email": "faaland1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2018-01-11 01:43:57.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-10460 rpm: Skip packaging lustre init for systemd",
        "message": "LU-10460 rpm: Skip packaging lustre init for systemd\n\nDon't install the lustre init script on systemd systems.  For\ninstance, starting in RHEL7, SysV is obsolete, replaced by systemd.\nWe choose not to add a systemd script at this time, instead favoring\nan OCF Resource Agent script for starting lustre servers through\nPacemaker.\n\nInstalling the init script would result in SystemD generating a\nservice for it.  We would then need to ensure that the service is\nnever enabled, in production, so that it does not conflict with\nPacemaker.  We would also need to maintain the script in addition to\nthe Resource Agent; and we would need to ensure admins, who manage\nboth RHEL6 and RHEL7 systems, never start the service out of habit.\n\nThese considerations do not exist for some use cases, such as file\nsystems running on nodes without shared storage (e.g. for testing).\n\nThis patch was written for use at LLNL and likely is not sufficient\nfor general inclusion.\n\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I15f61d14fb8c02e438a5e1df08836b524d31af55\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
